WorldStage Newsonline– The Management of Air Peace on Thursday announced that the UAE Government had stopped the airlifting of passengers from Nigeria to Dubai as part of its COVID-19 measures. Air Peace Spokesperson, Mr Stanley Olisa, made the announcement  in a statement in Lagos. Olisa, however, said that flights bringing Nigerians back from UAE were not affected. According to him, to this end, Air Peace flight from UAE(Sharjah-Dubai) to Lagos is not affected. “Normal flights shall resume when the restriction is lifted from Feb. 28, 2021. “Our esteemed customers whose flights are disrupted by this development can send a mail to us via callcenter@flyairpeace.com for a possible reschedule,” he added. He expressed the management’s appreciation to its numerous customers for their continued patronage.